{
  "doc_id": "56693",
  "text": "As mentioned previously, another factor contributing to differences in study results is differentiation of physical activity domains. Researchers often distinguish between leisuretime and occupational activity in order to better capture change as individuals assimilate to US culture. The CWHS assessed total moderate or vigorous physical activity across different domains and did not yield estimates of physical activity in each domain, which prevented exploration of changes in various types of activities with acculturation. With this information, we anticipate that we may have observed changes in the various domains of activity, such as occupational and leisure time, similar to previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] ).",
